'''Cognac Skënderbeu''' is an Albanian [[cognac]] produced and degusted for the first time on September 1, 1967 by then government-owned Kantina Skënderbeu.<ref>[http://archive.koha.net/?id=8&arkiva=1&l=147025 Ringjallen prodhimet tradicionale shqiptare]</ref>

The alcohol is prepared and aged only in vats, tuns and barrels made by oak wood, which gives it its unique aroma, bouquet and special colour. Its main ingredients are: aged raki, mountain plants extract, processed fruit (grapes, lemon, black plum), ethyl alcohol, sugar syrup, flower honey, distilled water, caramel, etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://konjakskenderbeu.al/?fq=shqip&art=historiku&k=kemba&gj=en|title=Konjak Skenderbeu|publisher=}}</ref><ref>[http://www.monitor.al/dehje-shqiptare-3 "Dehje" shqiptare]</ref>

